---
import { withBase } from '../../utils/base'
---

<section class="sect" id="features">
  <div class="wrap">

    <p class="sect-eyebrow" data-reveal>Features</p>
    <h2 class="sect-heading" data-reveal>Everything you need.<br />Nothing you don't.</h2>

    <div class="feats" data-stagger>

      <div class="feat">
        <p class="feat-name">157,000x Faster</p>
        <p class="feat-desc">Gemfile parsing is 157,000x faster than Bundler. Native Rust parsing means no Ruby startup overhead.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feat">
        <p class="feat-name">No Ruby Required</p>
        <p class="feat-desc">Works on systems without Ruby installed. Perfect for Docker containers and CI/CD pipelines.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feat">
        <p class="feat-name">Binary pack.lock</p>
        <p class="feat-desc">MessagePack-based lockfile format. 33,000x faster parsing than Gemfile.lock.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feat">
        <p class="feat-name">Rails First</p>
        <p class="feat-desc">First-class Rails support with commands like <code>pack server</code>, <code>pack console</code>, <code>pack db</code>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feat">
        <p class="feat-name">Parallel Downloads</p>
        <p class="feat-desc">Uses Rayon for concurrent gem downloads. Install 50 gems in seconds, not minutes.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feat">
        <p class="feat-name">Plugin System</p>
        <p class="feat-desc">Extend Pack with shell scripts, binaries, or Docker containers. Your plugins, your way.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feat">
        <p class="feat-name">Offline Mode</p>
        <p class="feat-desc">Cached gems work without network. Set <code>PACK_OFFLINE=1</code> and keep building.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feat">
        <p class="feat-name">Native gem exec</p>
        <p class="feat-desc">Direct binary execution without <code>bundle exec</code>. <code>pack exec rails console</code> works instantly.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feat">
        <p class="feat-name">Docker Optimized</p>
        <p class="feat-desc">Multi-stage builds, volume caching, and no Ruby needed in build stage.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .sect {
    padding: var(--sp-24) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .sect-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
  }

  .sect-heading {
    font-size: clamp(var(--text-2xl), 4vw, var(--text-3xl));
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-12);
  }

  .feats {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-left: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .feat {
    padding: var(--sp-6);
    border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    transition: background var(--duration) var(--ease);
  }

  .feat:hover { background: var(--bg-subtle); }

  .feat-name {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-2);
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .feat-desc {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--fg-secondary);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .feat-desc code {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--fg);
    background: var(--bg-muted);
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 960px) {
    .feats { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .feats { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
